hree chemically distinct terminal pathways\u2014Strecker synthesis, Bucherer-Bergs hydantoin hydrolysis, and reductive amination of \u03b1-ketoisovalerate\u2014fed by multiple upstream routes to the key bottleneck intermediate isobutyraldehyde. The literature identifies this branched C4 aldehyde as the central challenge (Keefe, Newton, Miller 1995): its generation is kinetically disfavored relative to formaldehyde and acetaldehyde, explaining valine's consistent ~20-fold yield deficit versus glycine. Three independent routes to isobutyraldehyde are modeled: Fischer-Tropsch-type (FTT) synthesis on magnetite (McCollom et al. 1999), NiS-catalyzed aldol diversification of acetaldehyde (Preiner et al. 2023), and spark discharge radical chemistry (Parker et al. 2011). The keto acid pathway uses Fe(0)-promoted pyruvate formation (Muchowska, Varma, Moran 2019) combined with acetaldehyde condensation. All pathways incorporate environmental transitions (Hydrothermal\u2192Surface\u2192Biochemical) and specify mineral catalysts throughout. Hub molecules\u2014isobutyraldehyde, acetaldehyde, HCN, CO, and pyruvate\u2014create network density and redundancy.\",\n  \"molecules\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"mol_001\",\n      \"formula\": \"CO2\",\n      \"iupac_name\": \"carbon dioxide\",\n      \"common_name\": \"carbon dioxide\",\n      \"inchi\": \"InChI=1S/CO2/c2-1-3\",\n      \"role\": \"starting\",\n      \"environment_formed\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"mol_002\",\n      \"formula\": \"H2\",\n      \"iupac_name\": \"molecular hydrogen\",\n      \"common_name\": \"hydrogen gas\",\n      \"inchi\": \"InChI=1S/H2/h1H\",\n      \"role\": \"starting\",\n      \"environment_formed\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"mol_003\",\n      \"formula\": \"NH3\",\n      \"iupac_name\": \"ammonia\",\n      \"common_name\": \"ammonia\",\n      \"inchi\": \"InChI=1S/H3N/h1H3\",\n      \"role\": \"starting\",\n      \"environment_formed\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"mol_